Is it true to use Segwit only for transactions and not HODLers. Per Luke Dash, a bitcoin developer;

“As a reminder, you should NOT use #Segwit for non-Lightning wallets. It is harmful to #Bitcoin by enabling larger blocks and increasing the growing rate of centralisation. (This *includes* Bech32 addresses! Try to use 1xxx or 3xxx addresses you’re sure are not Segwit).”

Is this true?

efeixed.Text:
I agree. Bitcoin has become kinda like politics in that most people are so one sided, especially in bear and bull markets. The negativity nowadays is almost completely price driven, but the interesting thing is that development and news has been very positive overall in the last 6 months or so at least. 

&#x200B;

Bitcoin's price has never gone in the direction that it should based on it's advancements. Looking back at the bull run in 2017, it's absurd to think how many issues there were and nobody cared...issues that are since being solved or at least look to be in the near future. A knock on volume? Fine with me. That's what signals the consolidation period in previous bitcoin cycles. 

&#x200B;

The undeniable truth is that thousands of bitcoin wallets are created each day, and transactions are going up. Yet the current bears are like 2017 bulls, just seeing no possibility of a reversal. They truly believe that bitcoin will be under a $100 in 2 years. Which is really cute.
